column711: My most important career goal is to continue establishing strong paths in psychology and criminal justice that lets me use my own personal experiences to make a difference. I want more than just a job; I want a career where I can apply what I’ve learned to help those impacted by addiction and crime. This isn’t just about finding work for me, it’s about creating a fulfilling as well as sustainable life where I can make a positive impact. On a broader level, this goal ties into my desire for financial stability and independence. By pursuing criminal profiling, psychological rehabilitation, or even founding rehabilitation schools, I can work toward a future where I’m not only financially secure but also contributing something meaningful to society. Achieving this goal would mean that my work aligns with my values and experiences, helping me make a real difference while building a stable, purpose-driven life.
column713: I think my most important goal in learning and education would be to keep gaining a deep, practical understanding of psychology that I can use in becoming a skilled psychologist, etc. Doing well in my courses is essential, this is part of my broader goal: preparing myself to make a positive impact. My education goal is to complete my Psych. degree, continue on to a PhD, and build the expertise ill need for my future. I want to master the concepts and skills that will allow me to support and understand others in powerful, life-changing ways.
column717: My main goal in non-intimate relationships would be to build strong, supportive connections where we can offer each other encouragement and understanding. Ultimately, I want a reliable network of friends, family, and colleagues who contribute positively to my life and career and vice versa.
column723: My spiritual goal is to keep a positive, hopeful outlook. Something I’ve achieved through a lot of inner work. Meditation, forward-thinking, and vision boards help me stay focused on kindness and good energy. Now, I want to teach others how to reach this mindset and build their own foundation of positivity.
column725: My main self-growth goal is to become the best version of myself; resilient, confident, and compassionate. Since October 2019, I’ve consistently focused and directed effort on self-improvement and change.

column711: When I think about my career aspirations and the amount of money I'd hopefully make, I usually picture how I'd feel and what the rest of my life would look like outside of work. I don't have an exact career aspiration right now, or an amount of money that I see myself making but rather I hope to work and make enough money to the point where I don't have to be in constant worry. I want to be able to give moeny to those I love and have some disposable income for things I may not need, but want, and to be able to give back to my parents and loved ones without having to worry too much. As far as career goes, my only goal really is to not be miserable to get a last resort kind of position. I want to enjoy what I do to an extent and feel that whatever I end up doing is benefitting more than just me or the company I work for.
